    <h1>Dynamic Portfolio Choice</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">MIT OCW 18.S096 + 15.450 (CC BY-NC-SA 4.0)</p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">Static optimization picks weights once. <strong>Dynamic portfolio choice</strong> adjusts allocations over time as wealth, market conditions, and the investment horizon change. The Bellman equation turns a T-period problem into T one-period problems, each informed by the future.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- SVG: multi-period decision tree -->
